    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "In the end a fixed left menu only work if you limit the left menu items to a fixed number. The more they grow the more it will be hard to fit them all in the left column (thus weird scrollbars etc).\n\nAs for #411 I think I put what seemed obvious to me in it: big buttons and contrast at important spot while most users will not need them. Yes we need to show we are on github, not at a fixed css position I feel.\n",
